g.aria-label: This is an example of a partial order. A partial order is a collection of objects with an ordering relation. In this case the objects each have three gray faces that can each be colored yellow or green, or left gray. One such object A comes before another object B if we can change A into B by coloring zero or more of its gray faces. Once a face is colored it may not be changed. This ordering relation is denoted by the symbol. The right lattice gives a visual depiction of this ordering, and illustrates the concepts of a dense set, and an ideal.
